# Agent-generated tools live in their own nested git repo. The
# parent repo tracks only the .gitkeep placeholder so the directory
# survives a fresh clone; everything else (the nested .git/, every
# *.py the agent writes, __pycache__, etc.) stays out of the main
# history. NB: a directory-level ignore (`generated/`) would prevent
# git from descending into the folder to re-include the keepfile,
# so the glob form is required.
agent-daemon/tools/generated/*
!agent-daemon/tools/generated/.gitkeep
